  "prompt": "Is having too much sex going to debilitate my inmune system?",
  "response": "Having sex in moderation is generally considered a healthy part of adult life, and there is no scientific evidence to suggest that having sex too frequently will debilitate your immune system. In fact, some studies suggest that regular sexual activity may even have certain health benefits, including potentially boosting the immune system. \n\nHowever, excessive sexual activity can lead to physical discomfort and fatigue, and if it becomes compulsive or interferes with daily life and responsibilities, it may indicate an underlying issue. It's also important to practice safe sex to reduce the risk of sexually transmitted infections (STIs), which can impact overall health.\n\nIf you have specific concerns about your sexual activity and its effects on your health, it's a good idea to consult a healthcare professional. They can provide personalized advice based on your individual circumstances.",
